texts.text: >This city's economy had gone to crap, no-one left but old farts.
>With nothing to do, you wander, head buried in your phone.
>You walk past someone doing the same.
>What are you looking at? Is it the same thing I am?
>The hustle and bustle of Akiba. Touts for maid cafes...
>Office workers going home, school kids messing around...

>Where are you going?
Are you even going anywhere?
>The wave of bodies as people cross the crosswalk.

>So many people,
but you're alone in the crowd.
>Have you ever felt like that?
Thank you for downloading this application.
Do not be surprised. This game comes recommended by Megakin.
You were looking for some action, were you not?
Then this is your game.
Although it might be a little more than you expected.
I've finally found you, the chosen one, at last.
I was waiting for someone like you to download this game.

But where are my manners?
May I ask who you are?
All people keep demons. Some within. Others, on their sleeve.
Show me yours.
In this game, players summon demons to fight.
That's right. Demons.
In other words...
You'll be a "Devil Downloader".
What's your name?
Who the hell are you?
Now that you mention it...
not having some sort of name does make things inconvenient.
For now, you may call me "Einherjar".
Let's see how you do in a little sparring match against my demon.
No need to fear. This is only the Tutorial, after all.
Use the demon summoning (Dx2) app to try summoning a demon.
A new war is brewing. Against a previously unknown life form.
While we do not yet know whether its intentions are evil,
you must do battle against its followers.

That life form is called VANITAS.
"God's tool for testing humanity".
There exists a group of those that follow Vanitas...
known as the ACOLYTES.
Opposing the Acolytes are the LIBERATORS... that would be you.
Oppose?
This is all too sudden...
Your fellow Liberators will fill you in on the details.
They're Devil Downloaders, [cus color=emphasis]Dx2[cus color=end] for short.
Like you, they also possess the ability to summon demons.
Their location is marked on your phone's map app.

It's a building in Akihabara.
Head over there.

Heyo, MegaTube.
This is Megakin comin' atcha.
Broadcastin' from an undisclosed location in Tokyo.
Aight, today's show is gonna be a little different.
Remember when I mentioned that weird game doin' the rounds?
It ain't that hard to figure out.
Not for you guys.
There's a battle goin' on, between THEIR game and OURS.
Don't let THEM make the rules.
That's all I gotta say about that.
Wassup!
So you're the new Dx2, huh?
You one of those quiet types that's actually a total psycho?
Hah! I'm just messin' with ya.

What's with that reaction?
Some people got no sense of humor.
Wait. You're THE Megakin?
Someone thinks they're funny.
The Liberators and the Acolytes are at war, yo.

And we be the Liberators.
You already know this, yeah?
And this place, this is the Liberators' Tokyo Branch.

I'm in charge around here.
Aight?
Your face, it's perfect for some target practice.

Please don't misunderstand.
I mean it as a compliment.

That's Rika Ryuzouji.
One of the Liberators.
Her codename is "Templar Dragon".
One day, I'll build a cabin out in the great outdoors,
so I can shoot my guns off while getting wasted.
She's kinda weird, but that's her way of saying hello.
Anyways, welcome to the Tokyo Branch!
You should check in with the boss, Einherjar.
You can get in touch with him via that computer over there.
It appears you made it to the Tokyo Branch in one piece.
Allow me to express again our warmest welcome, [sys user_name].
Welcome to the Liberators.
To begin, I have several directives for you to carry out.
Have you confirmed your Order Missions?
Completing them will [cus color=emphasis]unlock various functions[cus color=end].
Demon Fusion, Summons, Enhancements and more...

It's almost like a game, no?
That's because this is a game.
Just like I said.
And according to this game's rules, you'll need some funds to get started.
This will help in your fight against the Acolytes. Take it.
I wish you the best of luck, [ [sys user_name] ].
And hope that you can put an end to the Acolytes evil designs.
Finished talkin' with the boss?
Aight, that's enough for today.
Demons, Dx2, Liberators...
We really threw ya in the deep end. I reckon you've had enough.
Let's continue this later. Come to Akihabara when you're ready.
But don't take too long, aight?
You're part of a different world now. And we ain't got no time to waste.
